				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rytan,
<br />

<br />
Thank you for the logical post.  The only correction i would make is that if you're comparing mana regen, mages are generally nice people, and tend to give rods to any other casters that might be in the area. I'd ask that you remove "public" mana regen components from the equation for a better comparasin.
<br />

<br />
On paper, taken by itself, those numbers are indeed quite out of balance. However, without that "out of balance" mana regen, which direction do you foresee magician DPS headed in? As <span style="font-style: italic">respected damage dealers</span> which direction should Magician DPS be headed in relative to other DPS classes? <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" /> Where I'm going with these questions is that while our mana regen seems out of whack, our DPS has never seemed very unbalancing (at least from our perspective). How do you foresee a DPS only class getting groups after taking a hit to DPS?
<br />

<br />
Extending the mana regen on the Xegony line is a nice start, but please consider adding a mana regen component to the lower level phantom armor spells as well. Without pet canni, mages in their low 50's will really be hurting.
<br />

<br />
On a more personal note, I started with, and stuck with playing a mage because of the good solo ability of the class. Can you please consider adressing the impact on solo'ers? For people who can only play for an hour or so at a time, this is not a pleasant change. 
<br />

<br />
Thanks,<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1002541&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Naladini Dreamfyre</a>
