			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">NOTE:  I'm editing this post to try and keep it up to date with other's suggestions.
<br />

<br />
Your numbers seem accurate, but there are a few other factors you're leaving out:
<br />

<br />
1) AA cost of those mana regen bonuses.  Chanters need to spend 5AA to get gather mana, Wizards 3AA for HoD, but mages must spend 18 for Water Form 3 (which, incedentally, is worse for mana regen than either of the others).  Also, quick summoning 3 (which you assume for your analysis of pet canni mana regen) costs 18AA (canni w/o QS, using only haste ring, is ~103mana/tick).  Please don't judge the entire mage community on what the best of us are capable of.
<br />

<br />
2) Other effects of Pet-Canni.  While canni'ing, mage pets are not doing DPS -- and we lose a significant amount of our effectiveness.  Your comparison here leaves out that disadvantage to pet canni.
<br />

<br />
3) Mod Rods.  Sure, a mage can get 7.2 mana/tick from consistent use of rods.  Unfortunately, most of the rest of the group also wants that 7.2 mana/tick.  Only the enchanter has a sharable form of mana regen akin to the mod rod, and theirs is clearly far more mana efficient.  I think that for most mages modrods (and keeping the group fresh on them) is a mana sink, not a mana source.
<br />

<br />
4) Stacking issues.  Pot9 specifically.  It stacks with all other robe-caster mana regen, but not with Xegony's guard.  With a druid in the group, we suffer drastically compared to others.
<br />

<br />
5) Passivity of regen.  All other regen components that are being compared are completely passive (with the possible exception of the health DoT of the huge necro mana regen).  In order for a mage to take advantage of pet-canni, it requires full attention and excludes any other activity.
<br />

<br />
6) (hardest to present)  Balance!  Mages give up a lot to have pets.  Others have very comparable pets without giving up nearly as much (slow and buffs for BST; snare, FD, and great easy mana regen for NEC).  Pet-canni (and the ability to have the fastest mana regen in the game) has always seemed like a decent compensation for this.  Now mages just seem lacking.
<br />

<br />
This change seems just a bit overwhelming.  Why completely negate one of the largest mage advantages like this?  It seems that some sort of less drastic approach would be more appropriate.  How about a 80 mana cap per-reclaim?  That gives ~66mana/tick regen, with the requirement of QS3, Rathe's Son, and no pet doing damage.
<br />

<br />
This is just a bit of a bomb being dropped on mages... disappointing to see one of my standard crutches being simply removed.
<br />

<br />
- Nemuneir Noldaron
<br />
Arch Convoker from Ayonae Ro</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Nemuneir on Wed Dec 17, 2003 6:53 am; edited 4 times in total</span></td>
