<br />

<br />
Mod rod needs mana for casting subtracted to get net mana gain. (looks like this may have been the case on all spells BTW)
<br />

<br />
Pet canni needs spread out in time over dump time as it can only be used by taking the magician out of combat or when on down time. Note you did use re-use time for mod rod, harvest, etc. and should have for pet canni also.
<br />

<br />
Typical for me in LDoN was SM2 pet pet SM2 or a net of about 360 mana in 25 sec. When combat time is added it's more like canni time is 20 % of the time (estimate). So for me it was an effective FT of about 17  from doing pet canni. Solo it means I can get 20% of an AA an hour instead of less than 10% of an AA.
<br />

<br />
Look at time to fill mana bar for a mage and then time to dump since pet-canni is only avail out of combat. (Note you may need to do this for other classes as I don’t know them well.)
<br />

<br />
I’m at home so I can not open the following but use them to get how long it takes to dump mana for poorly equipped and well equipped magician without any other mana regen. Use this with the other pet canni sheet to get how long to get the mana back. Now you have a total time to use the mana and get the mana back giving a true effective FT number. 
<br />

<br />
Damage Sheet
<br />
<a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=54" target="_blank">http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=54</a>
