				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Rytan -
<br />

<br />
I don't think anyone is trying to argue that pet-canni gives some crazy mana regen.  I think that most of the points are that <span style="font-weight: bold">without</span> canni we have really dismal mana regen.  [edit] I am mistaken -- many posters do in fact contend (very rationally) that the mana regen of canni is not unreasonable.  [/edit]
<br />

<br />
You've hand-waved away some very valid points here by calling them all situational...
<br />

<br />
Xegony's doesn't stack with the druid Nine spells.
<br />

<br />
T-Rods cost mana for the entire group, not just for the mage.
<br />

<br />
The 4 mana/tick from Water Form 3 that you're including in all of your high-end calculations cost a whopping EIGHTEEN AA.  We're not talking a piddly time investment, and we are talking a very small overall mana regen improvement.
<br />

<br />
You make good points about future growth, but I would suggest to you that removal of pet canni requires a large amount of rebalancing of the mage class.  You can't simply remove an ability that is as powerful as you obviously think this is and expect it to have no effect on overall mage ability.  If you're claiming that mages were otherwise overpowered <span style="font-weight: bold">because</span> of pet-canni, I think you're very much mistaken.
<br />

<br />
- Nemuneir Noldaron
<br />
Arch Convoker of Ayonae Ro</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Nemuneir on Wed Dec 17, 2003 7:43 am; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
